---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import NeonCard from "@/components/NeonCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Principles | harder.dev" description="Guiding principles for AI and agentic experimentation.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="muted">/principles</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Principles</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">A few principles I keep coming back to after two decades of building software.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container grid grid-2">
      <NeonCard>
        <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;">1) Keep it understandable</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
          If a design takes a whitepaper to explain, it will be hard to maintain. Clear beats clever most days.
        </p>
      </NeonCard>
      <NeonCard>
        <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;">2) Guardrails before autonomy</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
          Before you give agents more room, add limits, visibility, and rollback paths. Slow is smooth, smooth is fast.
        </p>
      </NeonCard>
      <NeonCard>
        <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;">3) Let evidence lead</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
          Demos are useful, but measurements decide. Benchmarks, evals, and production behavior tell the truth.
        </p>
      </NeonCard>
      <NeonCard>
        <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;">4) Use trusted inputs</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
          Automate updates, but be picky about sources. A clean feed saves a lot of cleanup later.
        </p>
      </NeonCard>
      <NeonCard>
        <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;">5) Build for the next maintainer</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
          Write code and docs so future-you or a teammate can pick it up quickly. Kindness scales.
        </p>
      </NeonCard>
      <NeonCard>
        <h2 style="font-size:1.2rem;">6) Stay curious, stay practical</h2>
        <p style="margin-top:0.6rem;">
          I love new tools and ideas. I also like shipping. Explore boldly, then bring it back to useful outcomes.
        </p>
      </NeonCard>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
